'''Amazon.com Incorporated''', also known as '''Amazon.com, Inc''' or simply '''Amazon''', is an American multinational technology company.It is the parent company of [[Amazon MGM Studios]], of Amazon Music, of Amazon Prime Video, and of [[MGM]]. It was founded by Jeff Bezos in 1994.

Currently, it has the television rights of the books [[The Lord of the Rings]] and [[The Hobbit]], which acquired them from [[Tolkien Estate]].<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2017/11/14/amazons-250m-lord-of-the-rings-purchase-price-is-1000-times-what-tolkein-first-got-for-it/|articlename=EAmazon's $250M 'Lord Of The Rings' Purchase Price Is 1,000 Times What Tolkien First Got For It|dated=14 November 2017|website=[https://www.forbes.com/?sh=67e03c012254 https://www.forbes.com/]|accessed=10 October 2022}}</ref>

